{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Carve"], "type": "title", "extent": [31, 41], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [41, 117], "text": ["Slices, cuts or extracts points or cross-sections from a primitive."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [117, 390], "text": ["This tool works best with NURBS, meshes, and Beziers because it treats the whole object as a primitive, unlike polygons which have many separate primitives. For example, you can use this tool to slice up a watermelon, or to slice up a curve and animate the cut over time."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "extent": [420, 468], "text": ["Select the faces or hulls to carve."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "extent": [468, 555], "text": ["Click the ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SOP/carve", "scheme": "Icon", "type": "link", "value": "SOP/carve"}, {"text": ["Carve"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/carve", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/carve"}, " tool on the ", {"text": ["Model"], "type": "ui"}, " tab."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "extent": [555, 653], "text": ["Specify what to slice, cut, or extract using the ", {"text": ["parameter editor"], "fullpath": "/ref/panes/parms", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/ref/panes/parms"}, ". "]}], "container": true, "type": "ord_group"}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [653, 690], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/shelf/carve.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/shelf/carve.png"}]}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Using Carve"], "extent": [390, 420], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": "includeme"}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [690, 777], "text": ["For specific parameter help see the ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SOP/carve", "scheme": "Icon", "type": "link", "value": "SOP/carve"}, {"text": ["Carve"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/carve", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/carve"},